                     <interp inst="t18301209-160-person1449" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I received four half-crowns from Mr. Riley, and gave them to Jane Hodge, my servant.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-160-person1450">
                  JANE 
                  HODGE
               <interp inst="t18301209-160-person1450" type="surname" value="HODGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-160-person1450" type="given" value="JANE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-160-person1450" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On Tuesday, the 2nd of November, I was sent by Mr. Patterson to Mr. Riley's; I bought 1 lb. of 10s. tea of the prisoner, and paid him with four half-crowns I got from Mr. Patterson.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-160-person1451">
                  JAMES 
                  RUST
               <interp inst="t18301209-160-person1451" type="surname" value="RUST"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-160-person1451" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18301209-160-person1451" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner; I searched his box, in his presence, and found these two half-crowns, nine other half-crowns, four sovereigns, three half-sovereigns, and 16s. 6d.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Was the box open? A. It was not locked - Heritage was before the Magistrate; these were the two marked half-crowns.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18301209-160-person1452">
